The paper deals with obstacle avoidance in mobile robotics, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of probability measures and chance constraints suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and mixed integer linear programming suggests a connection to mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
